<p>
The sentence pattern A@HI{{@EM{{noha}}}}B@HI{{@EM{{da}}}} is used to offer some new and important information B about the topic A.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KT{{kurasu}}de@FG{{@KJ{{one^turn}}:ichiban'}}@KJ{{head}}gaii@EM{{noha}}@FG{{@KJ{{good*luck^rice*field}}:yoshida}}san@EM{{da}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The brightest one in this class is Mr. Yoshida.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The particle used with the noun or noun phrase between @HI{{@EM{{noha}}}} and @HI{{@EM{{da}}}} usually drops if it does not have a concrete meaning or the sentence is somehow predictable without it.
In this example the @HI{{ga}} after @HI{{@KJ{{forest^rice*field}}san'}} has dropped.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{eight^time}}uchini@KJ{{come}}ta@EM{{noha}}@FG{{@KJ{{forest^rice*field}}:morita}}san@EM{{da}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It was Mr. Morita who came to my house at eight o'clock.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

On the other hand, the particle is retained if it has a concrete meaning.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{forest^rice*field}}:morita}}gauchini@KJ{{come}}@EM{{noha}}@KJ{{car}}de@EM{{da}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It was by his car that Mr. Morita came to my house.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
The copula is usually in the present tense even if the @HI{{@EM{{no}}}} clause is in the past.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kinou@KJ{{buy}}tta@EM{{noha}}@KT{{sutereo}}@EM{{desu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It was a stereo that I bought yesterday.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
Normally the @HI{{@EM{{no}}}} clause takes and @HI{{@EM{{ha}}}}, marking the entire clause as old, presupposed, unimportant information.
However, the @HI{{@EM{{no}}}} clause can take @HI{{@EM{{ga}}}}, marking the clause as new, important information. In this alternative
construction, the information between @HI{{@EM{{noga}}}} and @HI{{@EM{{da}}}} contains unimportant information.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ga@KJ{{make}}tteiru@EM{{noga}}@KT{{robotto}}@EM{{desu}}.}}
